act.article:
2 Definitions. In these rules, unless the context otherwise requires,
a Act means the Energy Conservation Act, 2001 (52 of 2001);
b Director General means the Director-General of the Bureau appointed under sub-section (1) of section 9 of the Act;
c Section means a section of the Act; and
d all other words and expressions used herein and not defined but defined in the Act, shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in the Act.
